content:
Configure the Case Feed Publisher with the Enhanced Page Layout Editor

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs), Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
To configure the Case Feed publisher: Customize Application

From the object management settings for cases, go to Page Layouts. Select Use Page Layout Editor to Configure Actions. Click Save.

Access the page layout editor by clicking Edit on a layout in the Case Page Layouts section or  and choose Edit detail view. In the palette, click Quick Actions. Drag actions to the publisher area. You can drag off actions you don’t want. Up to five or six actions are displayed; the rest appear in a More dropdown list.

If previously using the Case Feed Settings page, the actions list appears at the top of the publisher. The Answer Customer action has been divided into Email and Portal. Standard Chatter actions automatically appear, replacing Write Case Note. You can change their sequence and remove any you don’t need.

Custom actions must use publisher.js rather than interaction.js. The Case Detail page expands to full width, making it easier to see related lists and other information.

The enhanced page layout editor for the Case Feed publisher is different from the original settings page.

title: Configure Case Feed Publisher with Enhanced Editor
